          • [ - ] jefferee - member since 03-May-16

            This game is hard to predict. Aspas has been the X factor this season and he was well rested during this week. Sevilla play style is soak up pressure and probably hit on the counter. Celta will pressure from the blast of the whistle although Sevilla might want to hold on to possession and defend with 6-8 men behind the ball but Mariano is still the weak link in Sevilla team and this Sevilla have not been creating many chances as of late (Valencia(1 shot on target), Granada(2 shots on target), Lyon also the same thing. Anyone who scores first here might prolly win the game. Celta Vigo to win first half is kind of logical because Sevilla scores more of their goals in the second half.
